1. *Sređeno* je sve za putovanje. (Everything is sorted out for the trip.)
2. Moram da idem u kupovinu, treba mi nešto *sređeno*. (I have to go shopping, I need something arranged.)
3. Ona je veoma *sređena* osoba. (She is a very organized person.)
4. *Sređen* je stan pre nekoliko dana. (The apartment was cleaned a few days ago.)
5. Čekamo da se situacija *sredi*. (*Sređeno* is used here in the infinitive form, meaning "to be arranged/organized." We are waiting for the situation to be sorted out.)